Source: Russian Television (RTR), "Vesti" program, 21 Jul 1999, 20:00

Not a single new patient was hospitalized today in the Rostov region, but
there are 2 teenagers in the city of Ryazan with symptoms that fit the
profile of the disease. Both are from Rostov.
[This was carried under a broadcast headline of "Pandemic in the Rostov
Region". No news from the Stavropol Region.
I've just found Ryazan on the map and it is a region unto itself, with
Ryazan the city in Ryazan the region (an oblast?). It is north and west of
the Rostov and Stavropol regions, about halfway between Rostov and Moscow.
